Love the atmosphere this place holds.  Not too crowded, has Connect 4 and Jenga and a ping pong table. Basement features a beer pong table, two shuffleboards, and a photobooth. Bathrooms are also located downstairs with a communal washing area outside.  I've usually gone on the weekends, and the staff members are friendly and the DJ typically spins good music. The playlist may not cater to all ears, but it sets a nice mood.  As for the menu, the mixed drinks are pretty much the same as the rest of the Whiskey-named bars. (Whiskey Brooklyn, Whiskey Tavern, etc.) They're reasonably priced the kitchen offers a decent selection of american-bar foods.  Overall a great venue looking for that "chill/fun vibe"
